result.text:
遇建天下带路行，回答印尼大学生就“一带一路”倡议向我提出的两个问题。@FrontlineBJ 

In this interview, Indonesian university students asked me 2 questions.

1. What criteria or guarantees does the Chinese government seek prior to making investments and lending to developing nations like Indonesia, especially those in the face of potential repayment difficuties? 
2. Does the BRI impact the environment or sustainability and what are some of the measures does the initiative take to address sustainability concerns?

If you are interested in the answer, check this video.

Chinese Ambassador to Indonesia
legacy.name: 陆慷 LU Kang

result.text:
遇建天下带路行，与CGTN对谈雅万高铁与中印尼关系。@FrontlineBJ 

Jakarta-Bandung High-speed railway is a flagship project, a friendship product between China and Indonesia, a witness of the fast development of the two countries, and one of the successful examples of cooperation under the Belt and Road Initiative. 

Once inaugurated, it will bring to Indonesia:
-efficiency
-more opportunities, +30,000 jobs
-more economic growth points

We expect a brighter prospect in this bilateral relationship. If you look back to the development of this relationship, it was not only owing to the strategic guidance by our presidents, but also has been a result of the common interets, common aspirations of our two countries. 🇨🇳🇮🇩
